$ Excel: Home -> Styles -> Conditional Formatting -> Highlight Cells Rules -> Duplicate Values

Although named *Duplicate Values*, this functionality also allows to highlight *unique* values.

sa:
  → Microsoft/Office/Excel/GUI/Ribbon/tabs/Data/Data-Tools/Remove-Duplicates[Data -> Data Tools -> Remove Duplicates]

  → Microsoft/Office/Excel/functions/countif#xls-count-occurences-of-a-value[Formula to count occurence of a value]
